        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 11:43PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1143 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 5 miles southeast of Greene to 5 miles east of
Ryder to 4 miles north of Golden Valley. Movement was east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Minot, Garrison, Burlington, Surrey, Parshall, Berthold, Glenburn,
Stanton, Sawyer, Max, Riverdale, Des Lacs, Plaza, Carpio, Makoti,
Pick City, Foxholm, Ryder, Coleharbor, and Benedict.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
south central, southwestern, north central and northwestern North
Dakota.</instruction>
